    <text>
        <body>
            <head>108. Paper Prepared in the <orgName corresp="rec7Bg5QUDG0eHqgl">Department of
                    State</orgName>
                <note n="1" place="foot" type="source" xml:id="d108fn1">Source: Department of State,
                    Lot 16D0355, James <persName corresp="recoqpx2aNuHTDUHK">Timbie</persName>
                    Files, Box 1, <gloss target="#t_NST_1">
                        <rs type="event" corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">NST</rs>
                    </gloss> 1985–1992. Secret; Sensitive.</note>
            </head>
            <opener>
                <dateline rendition="#right">
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1985-07-11"
                        >July 11, 1985</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p rendition="simple_centre">MILESTONES IN DEVELOPING “MONDAY” PAPER FOR SUMMIT</p>
            <p>Our principal <rs corresp="recQ5xJqddmHqhjNl" type="topic">arms control</rs>
                objective for the Summit would be to obtain a joint communique specifying guidelines
                for the <gloss target="#t_NST_1">
                    <rs type="event" corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">NST</rs>
                </gloss> delegations’ negotiation of an agreement(s) on the lines of the Monday
                    paper.<note n="2" place="foot" xml:id="d108fn2">See <ref target="#d107">Document
                        107</ref>.</note> The more details that can be agreed prior to the Summit
                and incorporated into the communique (and/or into subsequent guidance to the
                negotiators), the better. Outlined below is a timetable working toward such a Summit
                communique.</p>
            <table cols="2">
                <row>
                    <cell>Date</cell>
                    <cell>Event/Action</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>July 16</cell>
                    <cell>Second round of <gloss target="#t_NST_1">
                            <rs type="event" corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">NST</rs>
                        </gloss> talks concludes</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>July 31</cell>
                    <cell>
                        <persName corresp="rece7NCQ7Hh9DICyN">Shultz</persName>-<persName
                            corresp="reczYQHQnMCD2hSLc">Shevardnadze</persName> meeting(s) in
                        Helsinki; outline and discuss trade in general terms, i.e. deep and
                        continuing <rs type="topic" corresp="recHoFOsQcM4e5M4k">offensive arms</rs>
                        cuts in return for no development, testing or deployment of <rs type="topic"
                            corresp="recXBtz7WTz23HoT0">
                            <gloss target="#t_ABM_1">ABM</gloss> systems</rs> in contravention of
                            <gloss target="#t_ABM_1">ABM</gloss> Treaty as it currently
                        stands</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>August</cell>
                    <cell>Exchange messages regarding Moscow/Washington reactions to Helsinki
                        discussions; by end of August we should know whether Soviets are seriously
                        interested in deal</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>week of Sept 16</cell>
                    <cell>In preparation for <persName corresp="rece7NCQ7Hh9DICyN"
                            >Shultz</persName>-<persName corresp="reczYQHQnMCD2hSLc"
                            >Shevardnadze</persName> meeting at <gloss target="#t_UNGA_1">
                            <orgName corresp="reccsaN6k727DagWu">UNGA</orgName>
                        </gloss>, pass to Soviets (through <persName corresp="rec62rNu2glRunbNq"
                            >Dobrynin</persName>) non-paper regarding the sorts of reductions we
                        have in mind for strategic and <gloss target="#t_LRINF_1">
                            <rs type="topic" corresp="reczU3lVS4eZr8vxf">LRINF</rs>
                        </gloss> systems</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>Sept 19</cell>
                    <cell>Third round of <gloss target="#t_NST_1">
                            <rs type="event" corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">NST</rs>
                        </gloss> talks begins (<gloss target="#t_NST_1">
                            <rs type="event" corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">NST</rs>
                        </gloss> delegation not to address Monday package)</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>late Sept</cell>
                    <cell>
                        <persName corresp="rece7NCQ7Hh9DICyN">Shultz</persName>-<persName
                            corresp="reczYQHQnMCD2hSLc">Shevardnadze</persName> meeting(s) at <gloss
                            target="#t_UNGA_1">
                            <orgName corresp="reccsaN6k727DagWu">UNGA</orgName>
                        </gloss>; specific discussion of numbers of offensive arms and of strict
                        agreed interpretation of <gloss target="#t_ABM_1">ABM</gloss> Treaty
                        (including <gloss target="#t_ABM_1">ABM</gloss>
                        <rs corresp="recMjLDCnI9cLa32M" type="topic">Treaty compliance</rs> issues
                        and demarcation between permitted research and prohibited
                        development)</cell>
                </row>
                <pb facs="0432" n="404" xml:id="pg_404"/>
                <row>
                    <cell/>
                    <cell>
                        <persName corresp="reczYQHQnMCD2hSLc">Shevarnadze</persName> in Washington
                        for further discussions with <persName corresp="rece7NCQ7Hh9DICyN"
                            >Shultz</persName> and meeting with <persName
                            corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">President</persName>
                    </cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>early-mid Oct</cell>
                    <cell>Follow up September meetings through messages</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>week of Oct 21</cell>
                    <cell>Presidential letter to key <rs type="compound-subject"
                            corresp="recydYSQ1GmGAh8yu">Allied</rs> heads of government advising of
                        Monday discussions; SCG looks at emerging <gloss target="#t_INF_1">
                            <rs type="event" corresp="recgLCwFE47waxYP9">INF</rs>
                        </gloss> position (presented as possible new US proposal vice reference to
                        Monday discussions)</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell/>
                    <cell>Sides exchange draft Summit communique language for consideration at
                            <persName corresp="rece7NCQ7Hh9DICyN">Shultz</persName>-<persName
                            corresp="reczYQHQnMCD2hSLc">Shevardnadze</persName> meeting</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>week of Oct 28</cell>
                    <cell>
                        <persName corresp="rece7NCQ7Hh9DICyN">Shultz</persName>-<persName
                            corresp="reczYQHQnMCD2hSLc">Shevardnadze</persName> meeting in Moscow to
                        tackle remaining large issues and work communique language</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>early November</cell>
                    <cell>Continuing work on large issues and communique language (<persName
                            corresp="rece7NCQ7Hh9DICyN">Shultz</persName>-<persName
                            corresp="reczYQHQnMCD2hSLc">Shevardnadze</persName> channel)</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>November 19–20</cell>
                    <cell>Summit meeting in Geneva</cell>
                </row>
            </table>
            <p>Two further issues need to be addressed:</p>
            <p>—when <persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">the President</persName>/<persName
                    corresp="rec2p5eZ5kgeXCRJ4">McFarlane</persName> should inform <persName
                    corresp="recg0WDsRQgtuIKMw">Weinberger</persName>, <persName
                    corresp="rec6ieVf7pAFcijbs">Vessey</persName>, <persName
                    corresp="rec7YPjp5UCcrZuXE">Casey</persName>, <persName
                    corresp="recJYLsVHtwd9Q6nh">Adelman</persName> and <gloss target="#t_NST_1">
                    <rs type="event" corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">NST</rs>
                </gloss> negotiators of Monday discussions; and</p>
            <p>—the <gloss target="#t_NST_1">
                    <rs type="event" corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">NST</rs>
                </gloss> delegations’ role (running two channels would be difficult and, while we
                should include the <gloss target="#t_NST_1">
                    <rs type="event" corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">NST</rs>
                </gloss> negotiators in the decision-process, we may prefer they not directly
                address the Monday discussions with the Soviets; however, whatever they do should be
                fully consistent with and supportive of the Monday discussions end-point).</p>
        </body>
    </text>
